  "texts": [
    "For example, a recent paper Pedersen et al. (2020) designed an ESG-efficient frontier with the highest Sharpe ratio for the ESG-adjusted CAPM, where the choice may lead to a positive, negative or neutral outcome.",
    "AI techniques can be considered decision tools with a straightforward application to the different stages of portfolio execution (see Figure 3).",
    "The ability to describe underlying market structures, process vast amounts of structural and nonstructural information, or capture the non-linearity between different variables makes AI a key role in handling market complexity.",
    "AI tools guide the portfolio manager through the entire process, from visualizing the market to identifying assets, constructing the portfolio, executing trades, and interpreting results.",
    "This contributes toward achieving trust in AI-driven portfolio management systems."
  ]
}